# Git Workflow

Never push directly to `main`. Always use a feature branch and open a PR for merge.

## Push workflow

1. Create a branch from `main`:
   ```bash
   git checkout main && git pull origin main
   git checkout -b <type>/<short-description>
   ```
   Branch naming: `feat/...`, `fix/...`, `chore/...`, `docs/...`

2. Commit changes on the feature branch.

3. Push the branch (not main):
   ```bash
   git push -u origin HEAD
   ```

4. Open a PR targeting `main`:
   ```bash
   gh pr create --title "..." --body "..."
   ```

5. Merge via PR (squash or merge commit per repo convention). Do not force-push to `main`.

## When the user asks to push

- Push to a **new branch**, then create a PR.
- Return the PR URL when done.
- Only push to `main` if the user explicitly overrides this rule.
